cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the concept of argumentation and proposes a new approach to selecting the most acceptable arguments based on their interactions. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves developing models for evaluating arguments. It also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as arguments are typically expressed in natural language. Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of acceptability and refinement of existing classes, which are related to cryptography and security (cs.CR) as well as data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
